---
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />

    <!-- Primary SEO -->
    <title>Andrew Coco | Web Strategy, SEO & AI Discovery Leader</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Andrew Coco is a growth and web strategy leader at Peacock / NBCUniversal focused on AI discovery, SEO, experimentation, CRO, and subscription growth." />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://www.andrewco.co/" />

    <!-- Open Graph -->
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://www.andrewco.co/" />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Andrew Coco | Web Strategy, SEO & AI Discovery Leader" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="Growth and web strategy leader at Peacock / NBCUniversal. Focused on AI discovery, SEO, CRO, and subscription growth." />
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://www.andrewco.co/andrew_coco.png" />
    <meta property="og:image:alt" content="Andrew Coco — Web Strategy Leader" />
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="Andrew Coco" />

    <!-- Twitter / X Card -->
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
    <meta name="twitter:title" content="Andrew Coco | Web Strategy, SEO & AI Discovery Leader" />
    <meta name="twitter:description" content="Growth and web strategy leader at Peacock / NBCUniversal. Focused on AI discovery, SEO, CRO, and subscription growth." />
    <meta name="twitter:image" content="https://www.andrewco.co/andrew_coco.png" />

    <!-- Schema -->
    <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Person",
      "name": "Andrew Coco",
      "url": "https://www.andrewco.co",
      "image": "https://www.andrewco.co/andrew_coco.png",
      "jobTitle": "Senior Director of Web Strategy",
      "worksFor": {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "name": "Peacock / NBCUniversal"
      },
      "sameAs": [
        "https://www.linkedin.com/in/andrewcoco/"
      ],
      "knowsAbout": [
        "Web Strategy",
        "SEO",
        "AI Search Strategy",
        "Generative Engine Optimization",
        "Conversion Rate Optimization",
        "Experimentation",
        "Subscription Growth",
        "Media Digital Strategy"
      ]
    }
    </script>
  </head>

  <body>

    <header class="site-header">
      <div class="container header-inner">
        <a href="/" class="wordmark">Andrew Coco</a>
        <nav aria-label="Primary navigation">
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/andrewcoco/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
          <a href="/resume.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Resume</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main id="main-content">

      <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-heading">
        <div class="container hero-inner">
          <div class="hero-text">
            <p class="hero-eyebrow">Senior Director of Web Strategy · Peacock / NBCUniversal</p>
            <h1 id="hero-heading">Building growth systems<br />for the next era<br />of discovery.</h1>
            <p class="hero-sub">I lead web strategy, SEO, AI discovery, and experimentation programs that grow audiences and drive subscription growth at scale.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-photo">
            <img
              src="/andrew_coco.png"
              alt="Andrew Coco, Senior Director of Web Strategy at Peacock and NBCUniversal"
              width="320"
              height="320"
              loading="eager"
              fetchpriority="high"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section about" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
        <div class="container">
          <h2 id="about-heading" class="section-label">About</h2>
          <div class="about-body">
            <p>I'm a growth and web strategy leader who thinks about owned web as a competitive acquisition surface — not just a destination. My work connects search visibility, AI-driven discovery, experimentation, and conversion into a coherent system for growing subscription audiences.</p>
            <p>At Peacock and NBCUniversal, I lead strategy across SEO, AI discovery, acquisition landing experiences, and CRO — with a focus on durable, owned growth rather than purely paid channels. I'm particularly interested in how media companies adapt to shifting discovery environments while maintaining direct audience relationships.</p>
            <p>My background spans technical SEO, editorial ecosystems, experimentation frameworks, and product-minded web strategy. I think of myself as a strategist who happens to understand search deeply — not the other way around.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section focus" aria-labelledby="focus-heading">
        <div class="container">
          <h2 id="focus-heading" class="section-label">Focus Areas</h2>
          <ul class="focus-grid" role="list">
            <li class="focus-item">
              <h3>Web Strategy</h3>
              <p>Owned web as a growth and acquisition surface. Architecture, experience, and strategy aligned to business outcomes.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="focus-item">
              <h3>SEO & AI Discovery</h3>
              <p>Organic search and generative engine visibility. Building content and technical systems that perform across traditional and AI-powered discovery.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="focus-item">
              <h3>Experimentation & CRO</h3>
              <p>A/B testing and conversion systems that compound over time. Treating experimentation as an operating discipline, not a one-off tactic.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="focus-item">
              <h3>Subscription Growth</h3>
              <p>Acquisition funnel strategy for media and subscription products. From discovery to trial to loyal subscriber.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="focus-item">
              <h3>Acquisition Surfaces</h3>
              <p>Designing and optimizing the landing experiences, editorial surfaces, and owned channels that convert attention into audience.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="focus-item">
              <h3>Growth Systems</h3>
              <p>Cross-functional programs that connect search, content, product, and analytics into scalable, measurable growth engines.</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section thinking" aria-labelledby="thinking-heading">
        <div class="container">
          <h2 id="thinking-heading" class="section-label">What I'm Thinking About</h2>
          <p class="thinking-intro">Topics I'm actively working through — some will become essays, frameworks, or talks.</p>
          <ul class="thinking-list" role="list">
            <li>AI search as the next discovery layer — and what it means for owned web strategy</li>
            <li>Why experimentation is a growth operating system, not a testing function</li>
            <li>The changing role of SEO in a world where AI answers before users click</li>
            <li>How media companies should think about acquisition surfaces beyond paid channels</li>
            <li>Why owned web still matters in subscription growth</li>
            <li>Visibility across Google, AI assistants, YouTube, Reddit, and owned platforms</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section background" aria-labelledby="background-heading">
        <div class="container">
          <h2 id="background-heading" class="section-label">Background</h2>
          <div class="background-body">
            <div class="role current-role">
              <span class="role-badge">Current</span>
              <div class="role-detail">
                <strong>Senior Director, Web Strategy</strong>
                <span class="role-company">Peacock / NBCUniversal</span>
                <p>Leading web strategy, SEO, AI discovery, acquisition landing experiences, and experimentation programs across Peacock and NBCUniversal properties.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="role-context">
              <p>My career has been built at the intersection of search, editorial, and growth — working across media, subscription, and digital product environments. I've led technical SEO programs, built experimentation frameworks from the ground up, and developed acquisition strategies for some of the largest media brands in the country.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section contact" aria-labelledby="contact-heading">
        <div class="container">
          <h2 id="contact-heading" class="section-label">Get in Touch</h2>
          <p class="contact-intro">Open to conversations about web strategy, AI discovery, media growth, and the future of owned web.</p>
          <div class="contact-links">
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/andrewcoco/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="contact-btn">Connect on LinkedIn</a>
            <a href="/resume.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="contact-btn contact-btn--secondary">Download Resume</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </main>

    <footer class="site-footer">
      <div class="container footer-inner">
        <p class="footer-name">Andrew Coco</p>
        <p class="footer-copy">&copy; 2025 · andrewco.co</p>
      </div>
    </footer>

  </body>
</html>